00:12:07.040 --> 00:12:08.670
So let's write that down.

00:12:08.670 --> 00:12:14.570
So I'm going to make my basis
that I'm going to change to is

00:12:14.570 --> 00:12:20.460
going to be v1, v2, and v3.

00:12:20.460 --> 00:12:25.340
So just to make sure we
understand what we're doing,

00:12:25.340 --> 00:12:27.080
each of these vectors,
what do they look

00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:28.930
like in my new basis?

00:12:28.930 --> 00:12:35.690
Well v1 is equal to 1 times
v1, plus 0 times v2,

00:12:35.690 --> 00:12:38.720
plus 0 times v3.

00:12:38.720 --> 00:12:45.840
So v1, in my new basis, where v1
is the first basis vector,

00:12:45.840 --> 00:12:49.880
